    "question": "Why do birds flock?",
    "model": "perplexity.ai",
    "date": "2023-04-10",
    "answer": "Birds flock together for various reasons, including safety, warmth, and finding food[1][2][3][4]. Flocking can help birds avoid predators, share body heat, and locate food sources more efficiently. Flocking behavior can also be a way for birds to socialize and communicate with each other. The coordinated movements of birds in a flock are thought to be the result of each bird following simple rules based on the movements of its neighbors[5].\n",
